Here is a Java program that calculates factorial both recursively and iteratively:

```java
public class FactorialCalculator {

    // Recursive method
    public static long factorial(int n) {
        if (n < 0) throw new IllegalArgumentException("Number must be non-negative");
        if (n == 0 || n == 1) return 1;
        return n * factorial(n - 1);
    }

    // Iterative method
    public static long factorialIterative(int n) {
        if (n < 0) throw new IllegalArgumentException("Number must be non-negative");
        long result = 1;
        for (int i = 2; i <= n; i++) result *= i;
        return result;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int input1 = 5;
        System.out.println("Input: " + input1);
        System.out.println("Output: " + factorial(input1) + " (factorial of " + input1 + ")");

        int input2 = 7;
        System.out.println("\nInput: " + input2);
        System.out.println("Output: " + factorial(input2));

        System.out.println("\nAdditional Examples:");
        for (int i = 0; i <= 10; i++) {
            System.out.println("Factorial of " + i + " = " + factorial(i));
        }
    }
}
```
